---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lede = "Open to full-time roles from Senior IC through Director, and to contract, fractional, or workshop engagements while the search runs. Remote or hybrid, Kansas City base, no relocation.";

const bodyHtml = `<h2>Full-time roles</h2><p>Open to Work titles: Senior Product Designer, Staff Designer, Principal Designer, Design Systems Manager, UX Manager, UX Director.</p><p>Best fit is a team building in a regulated or high-consequence domain — healthcare, fintech, infrastructure, AI tooling, government — or a team standing up the AI design pipeline work that ties design systems to model-generated UI. Past employers have been Cerner and Oracle Health; the lessons travel.</p><p>Not a fit: full relocation out of Kansas City, or on-site five days a week.</p><h2>Contract and fractional</h2><p>Available for design-system audits, AI design pipeline prototyping (RAG + vector database + MCP server, integrated with whatever generation surface you're using), and fractional UX leadership for teams without a head of design. Typical engagements run six to twelve weeks for an audit or prototype, longer for fractional leadership.</p><p>Day rates on request.</p><h2>Workshops and advisory</h2><p>Half-day or full-day formats:</p><ul><li><strong>AI design pipelines.</strong> What a RAG-backed pipeline looks like end to end, where it tends to fail, and what your design org has to produce to feed it.</li><li><strong>Domain Foundation methodology.</strong> Encoding institutional design expertise as layered, machine-readable knowledge an AI can reason with. The case study lives at <a href="/work/domain-foundation/">/work/domain-foundation/</a>.</li><li><strong>Design-system governance.</strong> What I learned across three and a half years on Terra at Cerner — the gap between standards and shipped components, and the practices that close it.</li></ul><p>Best fit for design leadership, design-system teams, and product orgs trying to figure out where AI fits in their tooling without burning a quarter.</p>`;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Work with me — Jeremy Fuksa"
  description="Available for full-time roles from Senior IC through Director, plus contract, fractional, and workshop engagements. Kansas City, remote-friendly."
>
  <article class="about-page">
    <header class="about-header">
      <h1>Work with me</h1>
      <p class="about-lede">{lede}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="post-prose about-prose" set:html={bodyHtml} />

    <section class="about-cta-section">
      <h2 class="about-cta-title">Get in touch</h2>
      <p class="about-cta-body">Email is the fastest path. Tell me which of the three above fits — or that none of them does, and what you're actually trying to do.</p>
      <div class="about-cta-actions">
        <a href="mailto:hello@jeremyfuksa.com" class="hero-cta">Email me</a>
        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/jeremyfuksa" class="hero-cta-secondary">LinkedIn &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
